.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_ObjectTooltip
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: This adds a UI element into the World Space that can be used to provide additional information about an object by providing a piece of text with a line drawn to a destination point.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks: There are a number of parameters that can be set on the Prefab which are provided by the VRTK_ObjectTooltip script which is applied to the prefab.
.NET Framework 3.5.example: VRTK/Examples/029_Controller_Tooltips displays two cubes that have an object tooltip added to them along with tooltips that have been added to the controllers.

methods.name: OnEnable()
ResetTooltip()
methods.summary: The ResetTooltip method resets the tooltip back to its initial state.

methods.name: UpdateText(string newText)
methods.summary: The UpdateText method allows the tooltip text to be updated at runtime.

params.value: A string containing the text to update the tooltip to display.

events.name: ObjectTooltipReset
events.summary: Emitted when the object tooltip is reset.

events.name: ObjectTooltipTextUpdated
events.summary: Emitted when the object tooltip text is updated.
